<h1>Rules</h1>
<ul>
    <li>The first row of your CSV must be headers.</li>
    <li>The first column's header must be 'Filename'.</li>
    <li>The first column must be populated for each row.</li>
    <li>To upload more than one bitstream at a time, separate the filename in the first column with '|' (e.g. photo1.tif|photo2.tif)</li>
    <li>You can have as many header duplicates as you want so long as they are valid.</li>
    <li>You can zip a directory which contains all your files. It must be one directory and it's name should not start with '.', '_', or '-'</li>
    <li>The collection ID can be found by logging into <a href="<%= DspaceTools::Conf.dspace_repo %>"> repository</a>, selecting the desired collection, and then clicking on "edit collection" from the Context menu.  The collection ID will appear at the end of the web address.</li>
</ul>
</section>
